  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 180°C/ 160°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Deseed your<strong> peppers</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Add the <strong>pepper strips</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min until roasted and golden – these are your <strong>roasted peppers</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-mixed-pepper-and-chive-risotto-df/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>in 750ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[975ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1.4L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, then add your<strong> tomato paste</strong>, <strong>Chinese rice wine </strong>and <strong>red chilli relish</strong> – this is your<strong> sweet tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-mixed-pepper-and-chive-risotto-df/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4 min until softened but not browned</p><p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-mixed-pepper-and-chive-risotto-df/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add your <strong>arborio rice</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika</strong> and your <strong>ground turmeric</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min further</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-mixed-pepper-and-chive-risotto-df/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sweet tomato stock</strong> a ladle at a time, stirring continuously for 25-30 min or until all of the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked – this is your <strong>risotto</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-mixed-pepper-and-chive-risotto-df/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>chives</strong> finely</p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar flavour block[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-mixed-pepper-and-chive-risotto-df/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once cooked, remove the <strong>roasted</strong> <strong>peppers</strong> from the oven</p><p>Stir <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>roasted peppers</strong> into the risotto (save the rest for garnish!)</p><p>Remove the<strong> </strong>risotto from the heat and stir in<strong> half</strong> the <strong>grated cheeze </strong>and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped chives </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), then season with a grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>sweet mixed pepper & chive risotto</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-mixed-pepper-and-chive-risotto-df/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To serve, top the<strong> sweet mixed pepper & chive risotto</strong> with the <strong>reserved roasted peppers</strong>, <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>grated cheeze </strong>and your <strong>pine kernel & seed mix</strong></p><p>Garnish with the<strong> remaining chopped chives</strong> and a<strong> </strong>drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
